{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_6c7aef3d-c4bf-4b6f-8a05-2e070fbc0cd","tool_call":{"grepToolCall":{"args":{"pattern":"prospect|crm_connection","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm/docs","caseInsensitive":false,"multiline":false,"toolCallId":"tool_6c7aef3d-c4bf-4b6f-8a05-2e070fbc0cd","offset":0},"result":{"success":{"pattern":"prospect|crm_connection","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm/docs","outputMode":"content","workspaceResults":{"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm":{"content":{"matches":[{"file":"docs/implementations/prds/design_implementation_v1.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":42,"content":"1. **Manual-first → auto-follow-up.** A user writes and sends a _manual_ first email, then enrolls that prospect (and that exact thread) into an automated follow-up sequence whose steps thread under the original email.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":43,"content":"2. **Research-grounded AI generation.** Generate emails using up-to-date researched info on the prospect, their company, and a mapping of the sender's value proposition to that prospect.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":70,"content":"- **AI personalization at scale** — emails generated against prospect/company/role context, in 20+ languages; positioned as the differentiator vs. template-only tools.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":114,"content":"- **Manual-first flow**: compose/send first email (optionally AI-assisted) → enroll prospect + anchor thread into a follow-up sequence.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":153,"content":"- **C1.** Import prospects by CSV with column mapping (email, first/last name, company, title, custom fields).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":155,"content":"- **C2.** Pull prospects/accounts from a connected CRM into a list.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":156,"content":"- **C3.** View a prospect record: fields, CRM links, research profile, sequence history, message timeline.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":164,"content":"- **D5.** Enroll one or many prospects; choose sending mailbox(es); preview the schedule.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":165,"content":"  - AC: enrollment shows computed `nextRunAt` per step; can pause/resume/stop per enrollment or per prospect.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":169,"content":"- **E1.** Compose a one-off email to a prospect from a chosen mailbox (AI-assist optional). On send, Quiksend captures the **thread anchor** (Message-ID, thread id, mailbox).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":170,"content":"- **E2.** Immediately (or later) enroll that prospect into a **follow-up sequence**. Follow-up steps thread under the anchor: subject becomes `Re: <original>`, headers `In-Reply-To`/`References` set to the anchor, same mailbox.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":178,"content":"- **F2.** For a prospect, generate/refresh a **Research Profile**: facts about the prospect + company from CRM and live web research, with sources and a freshness timestamp.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":193,"content":"- **H2.** Create/update CRM contact when a new prospect is added; map fields per workspace config.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":200,"content":"- **I3.** Bounce detection updates prospect status and suppression.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":211,"content":"- **K1.** API keys (scoped per workspace) to create prospects, enroll into sequences, read analytics.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":212,"content":"- **K2.** Outbound webhooks on events (`message.sent`, `reply.received`, `enrollment.finished`, `prospect.unsubscribed`).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":301,"content":"Quiksend is component-dense — a drag-and-drop sequence builder, several data tables (prospects, sequences, analytics), a unified inbox, and many validated forms/settings. Re-implementing accessible dialogs, popovers, comboboxes, toasts, and focus management is undifferentiated work that's easy to get subtly wrong, so a library is worth it. The _copy-in_ kind (shadcn) is chosen over runtime-CSS-in-JS kits (MUI/Chakra) and batteries-included alternatives (Mantine/Ant) for three reasons:","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":313,"content":"- **Data grids:** compose **TanStack Table** (headless) with shadcn table primitives for prospects, sequence lists, analytics, and the inbox — sorting/filtering/pagination/virtualization, and it slots into the TanStack ecosystem already in use.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":378,"content":"export const prospect = pgTable(","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":379,"content":"  \"prospect\",","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":394,"content":"  (t) => [index(\"prospect_org_email_idx\").on(t.organizationId, t.email)],","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":445,"content":"    prospectId: uuid(\"prospect_id\").notNull(),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":456,"content":"    index(\"enroll_prospect_idx\").on(t.organizationId, t.prospectId),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":469,"content":"    prospectId: uuid(\"prospect_id\"),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":486,"content":"    index(\"message_prospect_idx\").on(t.organizationId, t.prospectId),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":494,"content":"  prospectId: uuid(\"prospect_id\"),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":532,"content":"export const crmConnection = pgTable(\"crm_connection\", {","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":665,"content":"This makes follow-ups land as genuine replies in the prospect's existing thread — exactly the behavior reps want and what protects deliverability.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":701,"content":"  if (await isSuppressed(e.org, e.prospect.email)) return finish(e, \"unsubscribed\");","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":723,"content":"        : renderTemplate(step, e.prospect, e.org);","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":726,"content":"        to: e.prospect.email,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":794,"content":"- Match inbound to a thread via `In-Reply-To`/`References` → `providerMessageId` of an outbound message → enrollment/prospect.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":796,"content":"- **Bounces:** parse DSN / provider bounce signals → mark message `bounced`, prospect `bounced`, add to suppression, terminate enrollment.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":813,"content":"Inputs:  prospect (email, name, title), company (name, domain), CRM fields (via Nango)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":826,"content":"The workspace `value_prop` library (products, positioning, proof points, ICP) is combined with the research profile so the model writes _why this sender is relevant to this specific prospect_ — not a generic pitch. This is the substance behind \"how our products are applicable to them.\"","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":848,"content":"      prospect: ctx.prospect,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":911,"content":"    if (event.type === \"connect\") saveCrmConnection(event); // → crm_connection row","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":922,"content":"Use Nango syncs to pull Contacts/Leads/Accounts incrementally; map into `prospect`/`company`. Pattern (Salesforce contacts shown; HubSpot analogous against `/crm/v3/objects/contacts`):","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":961,"content":"- **Contact upsert:** when a prospect is created locally, create/update the CRM contact per `field_mapping`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":966,"content":"- Nango → `/api/nango/webhook` notifies on new/updated records and sync completions → keep prospects fresh and trigger re-research if a prospect's role/company changed.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":967,"content":"- Field mapping is per-workspace JSON (`crm_connection.field_mapping`), editable in settings.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":986,"content":"// apps/web/src/routes/api/v1/prospects.ts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":987,"content":"export const Route = createFileRoute(\"/api/v1/prospects\")({","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1002,"content":"**Outbound webhooks:** HMAC-signed POSTs on `message.sent`, `reply.received`, `enrollment.finished`, `prospect.unsubscribed`, with retry + delivery log.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1020,"content":"- Per-workspace data retention controls; right-to-delete a prospect cascades.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1072,"content":"- **R-020** Schema + CRUD server fns for `company`/`prospect` (org-scoped).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1075,"content":"- _Exit (AC C1, C3):_ import a CSV, view prospects.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1079,"content":"- **R-030** `packages/integrations`: Nango node client wrapper; `crm_connection` model.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1081,"content":"- **R-032** Checkpointed contact/account syncs (SF + HS) → map into prospects/companies.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1100,"content":"- _Exit (AC D1–D5):_ build a sequence and enroll prospects; see computed schedule.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1136,"content":"- **R-100** Public REST API (`/api/v1/*`) with apiKey auth (prospects, enroll, analytics read).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1142,"content":"> **Suggested cutline for a usable internal alpha:** Phases 0–7 (you can run real manual-first + automated follow-ups with CRM-sourced prospects and a working inbox). Phases 8–10 complete the V0 differentiation (AI, write-back, API, compliance).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1150,"content":"1. ✅ **Manual-first → auto follow-up:** send a manual first email; enroll the prospect + that thread into a follow-up sequence; follow-ups send on schedule, threaded under the original, throttled per mailbox, and **stop on reply**.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1151,"content":"2. ✅ **Research-grounded AI generation:** generate a first email (and follow-ups) using live researched facts about the prospect + company and a mapping of the workspace's value prop, with human review.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"docs/implementations/phases/Quiksend-Implementation-Plan-Phases-2-10.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":41,"content":"  table needs it (prospects, sequences); everything else hard-deletes with cascade.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":55,"content":"  day-to-day prospect/sequence work is any member.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":113,"content":"| 2     | `company`, `prospect`, `list`, `list_member`, `import_batch`, `import_error`                                        |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":114,"content":"| 3     | `crm_connection`, `sync_state`; adds `crm_provider`/`crm_external_id`/`crm_connection_id` to `prospect` + `company` |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":128,"content":"`prospect` entities, CSV import with column mapping + dedupe, and a prospect detail view","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":138,"content":"- **`prospect`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `company_id` (nullable FK), `first_name`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":145,"content":"  list_id + prospect_id). Cheap now, needed by Phase 3 (\"pull contacts into a list\") and","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":170,"content":"  column to a prospect/company field or \"ignore\", remember mappings per org) → preview +","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":187,"content":"- **R-020** — `company`/`prospect`/`list` schema + migration; `orgFn` CRUD; tenancy tests.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":190,"content":"- **R-022** — prospect detail view: fields + inline edit, company panel, timeline shell","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":197,"content":"tenancy (org A can't read/update org B's prospects); keyset pagination stability.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":208,"content":"Import a CSV with a custom column mapping, land deduped prospects/companies, and view a","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":209,"content":"prospect with its (currently sparse) timeline.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":216,"content":"prospects/companies on an incremental, checkpointed basis, and stay fresh via webhooks.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":219,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 2 (prospect/company + `list`), Phase 1 (admin role gate, `orgFn`).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":231,"content":"- **`crm_connection`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `provider` (`salesforce`/`hubspot`),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":236,"content":"- **Extend `prospect` + `company`** with `crm_provider`, `crm_external_id`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":237,"content":"  `crm_connection_id`, `last_crm_sync_at`. Add unique `(organization_id, crm_provider,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":253,"content":"  prospect/company through the Phase-2 dedupe/upsert path, applying `field_mapping`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":262,"content":"- **Dedupe across sources:** an incoming CRM contact may match an existing prospect by","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":274,"content":"- **R-030** — `packages/integrations` Nango wrapper + `crm_connection`/`sync_state`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":279,"content":"- **R-032** — checkpointed contact/account syncs → mapped upsert into prospect/company;","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":299,"content":"update arrive via webhook and update the prospect.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":310,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 3 (Nango for Gmail/Microsoft OAuth), Phase 2 (send to a prospect).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":341,"content":"  `prospect_id`, `enrollment_id` (nullable, set by the engine), `direction`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":396,"content":"prospects (single + bulk) with mailbox round-robin and an accurate schedule preview.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":398,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 2 (prospects/lists), Phase 4 (mailboxes; templates that will send).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":411,"content":"  `sequence_id`, `prospect_id`, `mailbox_id` (round-robin assigned), `state` (the P6 state","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":413,"content":"  `ab_bucket`, timestamps. Unique `(organization_id, sequence_id, prospect_id)` — prevent","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":421,"content":"throttle/mailboxes/stop-on-reply). Enroll dialog: pick prospects or a list → preview the","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":462,"content":"prospects, and see a computed schedule.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":604,"content":"  `message_id_header` anchors (indexed in P4) to find the enrollment/prospect. Normalize","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":651,"content":"research a prospect (CRM + web), map to your value props, generate with structured","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":654,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 2 (prospect/company), Phase 6 (manual-first compose task is where","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":666,"content":"- **`research_profile`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `prospect_id`, `sources jsonb`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":672,"content":"- **`generation`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `prospect_id`/`enrollment_id`/`step_id`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":704,"content":"prospects → generations graded for grounding (claims traceable to sources), value-prop","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":732,"content":"- **`crm_writeback_log`** — `id`, `organization_id`, `crm_connection_id`, `event_type`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":733,"content":"  (`send`/`reply`/`status`), `entity` (prospect/message), `external_ref`, `status`,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":785,"content":"**Builds on.** Phase 1 (`apiKey` plugin), Phases 2/5/6 (prospects/enroll/analytics),","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":794,"content":"- *