{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_d3e25660-d199-498d-83aa-1ccb4397813","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs","query":"onConflictDoUpdate insert postgres unique index partial where"},"toolCallId":"tool_d3e25660-d199-498d-83aa-1ccb4397813","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Upsert Single Row in PostgreSQL, Cockroach, and SQLite\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/guides/upsert.mdx\n\nUse the .onConflictDoUpdate() method to insert a row or update it if a conflict occurs on the target column, such as a primary key.\n\n```typescript\nimport { users } from './schema';\n\nconst db = drizzle(...);\n\nawait db\n  .insert(users)\n  .values({ id: 1, name: 'John' })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: users.id,\n    set: { name: 'Super John' },\n  });\n```\n\n```sql\ninsert into users (\"id\", \"name\") values (1, 'John')\n  on conflict (\"id\") do update set name = 'Super John';\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Update on Conflict with targetWhere Clause in Postgres\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/latest-releases/drizzle-orm-v0308.mdx\n\nThis snippet demonstrates using `onConflictDoUpdate` with a `targetWhere` clause to specify conditions for the conflict target in PostgreSQL.\n\n```ts\nawait db.insert(employees)\n  .values({ employeeId: 123, name: 'John Doe' })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: employees.employeeId,\n    targetWhere: sql`name <> 'John Doe'`,\n    set: { name: sql`excluded.name` }\n  });\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Drizzle ORM onConflictDoUpdate with targetWhere and setWhere (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/cockroach/insert.mdx\n\nUse `targetWhere` and `setWhere` in Drizzle ORM's `onConflictDoUpdate` to specify conditional logic for conflict resolution, mirroring SQL's `WHERE` clauses.\n\n```typescript\nawait db.insert(employees)\n  .values({ employeeId: 123, name: 'John Doe' })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: employees.employeeId,\n    targetWhere: sql`name <> 'John Doe'`,\n    set: { name: sql`excluded.name` }\n  });\n\nawait db.insert(employees)\n  .values({ employeeId: 123, name: 'John Doe' })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: employees.employeeId,\n    set: { name: 'John Doe' },\n    setWhere: sql`name <> 'John Doe'`\n  });\n```\n\n### Upserts and conflicts > On conflict do update > where clauses\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/sqlite/insert.mdx\n\nWhen using `onConflictDoUpdate`, `where` clauses can be applied in two ways: `targetWhere` for conditions on the conflict target (useful for partial indexes) or `setWhere` for conditions on the update clause itself. This provides fine-grained control over conflict resolution logic.\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Fixes > Split `where` clause in Postgres `.onConflictDoUpdate` method\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/latest-releases/drizzle-orm-v0308.mdx\n\nThe `.onConflictDoUpdate` method in Postgres now separates the `where` clause into `setWhere` and `targetWhere` to better support different `on conflict ...` scenarios."}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_d3e25660-d199-498d-83aa-1ccb4397813","startedAtMs":"1782957295608","completedAtMs":"1782957302939"},"model_call_id":"33629d5d-d421-4b81-b0e8-701b7715f672-8-qnel","session_id":"0f3e4653-146e-4400-8c92-9cdee71cb418","timestamp_ms":1782957302999}
