{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_69382146-e191-4f1f-9172-e4af84082ae","tool_call":{"grepToolCall":{"args":{"pattern":"\"type\".*\"sync\"|WebhookPayload|sync.*webhook","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm/node_modules/.pnpm","glob":"**/nango*/**","caseInsensitive":false,"headLimit":40,"multiline":false,"toolCallId":"tool_69382146-e191-4f1f-9172-e4af84082ae","offset":0},"result":{"success":{"pattern":"\"type\".*\"sync\"|WebhookPayload|sync.*webhook","path":"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm/node_modules/.pnpm","outputMode":"content","workspaceResults":{"/Users/beckett/.cursor/worktrees/quiksend/phase-3-crm":{"content":{"matches":[],"totalLines":0,"totalMatchedLines":0,"clientTruncated":false,"ripgrepTruncated":false,"headLimitApplied":40}}}}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_69382146-e191-4f1f-9172-e4af84082ae","startedAtMs":"1782957462771","completedAtMs":"1782957464538"},"model_call_id":"33629d5d-d421-4b81-b0e8-701b7715f672-18-r1bf","session_id":"0f3e4653-146e-4400-8c92-9cdee71cb418","timestamp_ms":1782957464506}
{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_66514746-5bc2-42d4-95d9-4df81718303","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs","query":"pgEnum pgTable uniqueIndex partial index where sql references foreign key"},"toolCallId":"tool_66514746-5bc2-42d4-95d9-4df81718303","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Add Index to One-to-One Relation Foreign Key in Drizzle ORM (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/singlestore/relations-v2.mdx\n\nThis snippet demonstrates how to add an index to the `userId` foreign key in the `profile_info` table for optimal performance in one-to-one relationships.\n\n```typescript\nimport * as p from 'drizzle-orm/pg-core';\nimport { defineRelations } from 'drizzle-orm';\n\nexport const users = p.pgTable('users', {\n\tid: p.integer().primaryKey(),\n\tname: p.text(),\n});\n\nexport const profileInfo = pgTable('profile_info', {\n\tid: p.integer().primaryKey(),\n\tuserId: p.integer('user_id').references(() => users.id),\n\tmetadata: p.jsonb(),\n}, (table) => [\n  p.index('profile_info_user_id_idx').on(table.userId)\n]);\n\nexport const relations = defineRelations({ users, profileInfo }, (r) => ({\n\tusers: {\n\t\tprofileInfo: r.one.profileInfo({\n\t\t\tfrom: r.users.id,\n\t\t\tto: r.profileInfo.userId,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}));\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Schema with Foreign Key Reference (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/guides/seeding-using-with-option.mdx\n\nAdds a foreign key reference from `posts.authorId` to `users.id` to resolve the seeding error when using the `with` option.\n\n```ts\nimport { serial, pgTable, integer, text } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\n\nexport const users = pgTable('users', {\n\tid: serial('id').primaryKey(),\n\tname: text('name'),\n});\n\nexport const posts = pgTable('posts', {\n\tid: serial('id').primaryKey(),\n\tcontent: text('content'),\n\tauthorId: integer('author_id').notNull().references(() => users.id),\n});\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Comprehensive CockroachDB Schema Definition Example\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/cockroach/sql-schema-declaration.mdx\n\nA complete example demonstrating the definition of `users`, `posts`, and `comments` tables, including enums, primary keys, identity columns, foreign key references, and indexes.\n\n```ts\nimport type { AnyCockroachColumn } from \"drizzle-orm/cockroach-core\";\nimport { cockroachEnum, cockroachTable as table } from \"drizzle-orm/cockroach-core\";\nimport * as t from \"drizzle-orm/cockroach-core\";\n\nexport const rolesEnum = cockroachEnum(\"roles\", [\"guest\", \"user\", \"admin\"]);\n\nexport const users = table(\n  \"users\",\n  {\n    id: t.int4().primaryKey().generatedAlwaysAsIdentity(),\n    firstName: t.varchar(\"first_name\", { length: 256 }),\n    lastName: t.varchar(\"last_name\", { length: 256 }),\n    email: t.varchar().notNull(),\n    invitee: t.int4().references((): AnyCockroachColumn => users.id),\n    role: rolesEnum().default(\"guest\"),\n  },\n  (table) => [\n    t.uniqueIndex(\"email_idx\").on(table.email)\n  ]\n);\n\nexport const posts = table(\n  \"posts\",\n  {\n    id: t.int4().primaryKey().generatedAlwaysAsIdentity(),\n    slug: t.varchar().$default(() => generateUniqueString(16)),\n    title: t.varchar({ length: 256 }),\n    ownerId: t.int4(\"owner_id\").references(() => users.id),\n  },\n  (table) => [\n    t.uniqueIndex(\"slug_idx\").on(table.slug),\n    t.index(\"title_idx\").on(table.title)\n  ]\n);\n\nexport const comments = table(\"comments\", {\n  id: t.int4().primaryKey().generatedAlwaysAsIdentity(),\n  text: t.varchar({ length: 256 }),\n  postId: t.int4(\"post_id\").references(() => posts.id),\n  ownerId: t.int4(\"owner_id\").references(() => users.id)\n});\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Generated SQL Migration for Drizzle ORM Schema\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/latest-releases/drizzle-orm-v0110.mdx\n\nThis snippet shows the SQL DDL statements generated for the auth_otp and users tables, including table creation, primary keys, foreign key constraints, and index creation.\n\n```sql\n-- SQL migration\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS auth_otp (\n    \"id\" SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    \"phone\" character varying(256),\n    \"user_id\" INT\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (\n    \"id\" SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    \"full_name\" character varying(256)\n);\n\nDO $$ BEGIN\n ALTER TABLE auth_otp ADD CONSTRAINT auth_otp_user_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (\"user_id\") REFERENCES users(id);\nEXCEPTION\n WHEN duplicate_object THEN null;\nEND $$;\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS users_full_name_index ON users (full_name);\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Declare Self-Referencing Foreign Key in Drizzle ORM and SQL\n\nSource: https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/pg/indexes-constraints.mdx\n\nDeclare a foreign key that references a column within the same table. Due to TypeScript limitations, explicitly set the return type for the reference callback or use the standalone `foreignKey` operator.\n\n```typescript\nimport { serial, text, integer, foreignKey, pgTable, type AnyPgColumn } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\n\nexport const user = pgTable(\"user\", {\n  id: serial(\"id\"),\n  name: text(\"name\"),\n  parentId: integer(\"parent_id\").references((): AnyPgColumn => user.id)\n});\n\n// or\nexport const user = pgTable(\"user\", {\n  id: serial(\"id\"),\n  name: text(\"name\"),\n  parentId: integer(\"parent_id\")\n}, (table) => [\n  foreignKey({\n    columns: [table.parentId],\n    foreignColumns: [table.id],\n    name: \"custom_fk\"\n  })\n]);\n```\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE \"user\" (\n\t\"id\" serial,\n\t\"name\" text,\n\t\"parent_id\" integer\n);\n\nALTER TABLE \"user\" ADD CONSTRAINT \"user_parent_id_user_id_fkey\" FOREIGN KEY (\"parent_id\") REFERENCES \"user\"(\"id\");\n```"}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_66514746-5bc2-42d4-95d9-4df81718303","startedAtMs":"1782957463770","completedAtMs":"1782957469189"},"model_call_id":"33629d5d-d421-4b81-b0e8-701b7715f672-18-r1bf","session_id":"0f3e4653-146e-4400-8c92-9cdee71cb418","timestamp_ms":1782957469191}
